item.title: The new harry potter and the order of the phoenix
item.dc:creator: @Taios Taios
item.description:
@Taios wrote:

[quote=“lothy, post:8, topic:117971”]Harry Potter has gotten crap. It’s just like all of the TV shows here in Australia: Big brother, CSI, CSI Miami, and so on. They drag them out for too long (or make you wait for incredible lengths of time for the next movie/book, in Harry Potter’s case).
As for the books, she just goes on and on. Take the conversation between Dumbledore and Malfoy for example: it dragged on for a few pages.
I’ll read the last book when it comes out, but only so I can call it a series.
/rant

By the way, bootleg copies of movies are shit anyway - it’ll be a while before you can get a high quality copy. :p[/quote]

Yea, her books 5-6 aren’t too good. I reckon she’s starting to write for the films more. Like in the 5th it allows films to have great effects and so fourth but the book could have been scaled down once all the crap was taken out, to about 500 pages.

SO hopefully the films will be better :). But the books, the most important thing i think, will be more rubbish =(.
